23/03/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Russian Prime Minister Vladimir Putin kicks off a visit to Belgrade on Wednesday (March 23rd), meeting with senior officials and parliament members. Talks will focus on economic and energy co-operation, particularly the South Stream gas pipeline project, as well as the situations in Kosovo, the Middle East and Libya. Several intergovernmental agreements will be signed during the visit. Security in the capital is at the highest level, with thousands of police officers mobilised. (Tanjug, RTS, Beta, B92 - 23/03/11)
